ce\": \"Who might end up on a Wheaties box?\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 597, \"end\": 605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wheaties\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wheaties\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wheaties\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wheaties\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States will send over 500 athletes to Paris, but we have narrowed the list down to 10 that have the potential to steal the show.\", \"from\": 612, \"to\": 751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 616, \"end\": 629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9787968318242949, \"rank\": 0.021662481410515876, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 661, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.630750945531078e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"over 500 athletes\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 657}, {\"ngram\": \"the list\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 697}, {\"ngram\": \"the potential\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 732}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 750}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are our choices for the 10 breakout stars of the Paris 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our choices\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 772}, {\"ngram\": \"the 10 breakout stars\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 798}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 825}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are sports in the Olympics that are popular more than just once every four years, such as basketball, soccer, and tennis.\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 955, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 838, \"to\": 844}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 860}, {\"ngram\": \"basketball\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 934}, {\"ngram\": \"soccer\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 942}, {\"ngram\": \"tennis\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 954}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The beauty of the Games, though, is that they give us a chance to get invested in sports that do not usually get any time in the spotlight.\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 1095, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The beauty\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 966}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 979}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1009}, {\"ngram\": \"a chance\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1018}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1044}, {\"ngram\": \"any time\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1077}, {\"ngram\": \"the spotlight\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1094}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Taekwondo is one of those sports, and you may not know it, but the U.S. has traditionally been one of the better taekwondo nations in the world, ranking third all-time in medals and gold medals since it was added as a full medal sport in 2000.\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6214522641929557e-30, \"text\": \"Taekwondo\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those sports\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1129}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1168}, {\"ngram\": \"the better taekwondo nations\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1227}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1240}, {\"ngram\": \"third all-time\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1264}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1274}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medals\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"a full medal sport\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anastasija Zolotic became the first U.S. woman to win Olympic taekwondo gold in 2021, but she did not make the team this year after being upset in qualifying by Kristina Teachout.\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1342, \"end\": 1360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anastasija_Zolotic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anastasija Zolotic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anastasija_Zolotic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anastasija_Zolotic\"}, {\"begin\": 1503, \"end\": 1511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristina_Davis\", \"score\": 0.9994064333390336, \"rank\": 0.0005939191913960179, \"text\": \"Kristina\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristina_Davis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristina_Davis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first U.S. woman\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1388}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic taekwondo gold\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1418}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1457}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to Teachout, the U.S. will be sending three others to Paris, but none are more exciting thanCJ Nickolas.\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1588, \"end\": 1593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.630750945531078e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1533}, {\"ngram\": \"Teachout\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1545}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1555}, {\"ngram\": \"three others\", \"from\": 1572, \"to\": 1584}, {\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1603}, {\"ngram\": \"more exciting thanCJ Nickolas\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1637}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nickolas is ranked second in the world in his weight class, and he's no stranger to taking home the hardware on the biggest stage.\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Nickolas\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1648}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1678}, {\"ngram\": \"his weight class\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1698}, {\"ngram\": \"the hardware\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1748}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest stage\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's won gold in the Pan American Games three times (including doing so after sustaining a broken arm in the finals this past May), and he took home silver in the World Championships last year.\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1964, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1784}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pan American Games\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1810}, {\"ngram\": \"a broken arm\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1872}, {\"ngram\": \"the finals\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 1886}, {\"ngram\": \"home silver\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 1926}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Championships\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's accomplished this despite enduring heart surgery in 2020 and moving up in weight classes.\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 2059, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"heart surgery\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2018}, {\"ngram\": \"weight classes\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2058}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nickolas has the talent and the personality to be one of the big winners in Paris, and his potential clash with 6'6\\\" Italian nemesis Simone Alessio could be one of the must-watch moments of the Games.\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2137, \"end\": 2142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.630750945531078e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2178, \"end\": 2185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9999920035189949, \"rank\": 5.816361408737916e-06, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 2194, \"end\": 2208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Alessio\", \"score\": 0.9999801201895663, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Alessio\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Alessio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Alessio\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Nickolas\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2069}, {\"ngram\": \"the talent\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngram\": \"the personality\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2104}, {\"ngram\": \"the big winners\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2133}, {\"ngram\": \"his potential clash\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2167}, {\"ngram\": \"the must-watch moments\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2247}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2260}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a new era of U.S. women's soccer, and these Olympics will be the first real chance to showcase that.\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a new era\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. women's soccer\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2300}, {\"ngram\": \"these Olympics\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2320}, {\"ngram\": \"the first real chance\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2350}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gone are the old guard, like Megan Rapinoe, Carli Lloyd, and Alex Morgan, and in their place are new stars, such as Trinity Rodman, Naomi Girma, andSophia Smith.\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2398, \"end\": 2411, \